children.text: The Son Bhandar Caves in Rajgir derive their name and infamy solely from the enduring legend of a massive hidden treasure. Local lore claims that King Bimbisara of the Magadha Empire concealed his vast riches within the caves before his imprisonment by his son, using a now-undeciphered inscription on the wall as a secret "password" or key to a hidden passage. Despite the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) identifying the structure as a historical Jain monastic complex dating to the Gupta perio

Earth and Neptune, two planets in our solar system, could hardly be more different when it comes to wind and weather. About five billion years ago, our Sun was born in a colossal process of gravitational collapse, where a massive cloud of gas and dust collapsed in space. Through the immense heat and pressure in its core, the Sun began to undergo thermonuclear fusion, emitting light and warmth. This marked the beginning of a new star and was the starting point for the formation of our solar system.
